result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[ma/mk] Cases 21CF135, 21CF623, 21CF624, 21CM380,22CM10 called at 11:55am {This hearing is being conducted via Zoom videoconferencing.} 
Defendant Joseph A Reed appeared by zoom from RCI, in custody.  Attorney Cassi Nelson appeared by zoom for Joseph A Reed.  Attorney Theresa Beck appears via zoom for State of Wisconsin. 
The Court finds that the Zoom video conferencing system is sight and sound sufficient. 

Constitutional rights reviewed; maximum penalties recited.
Pleas of " GUILTY  " entered on Counts #1 and #2 of Case 21CF623
Pleas of " GUILTY  " entered on Counts #2 and #4 of Case 21CF624
Plea of " GUILTY  " entered on Count #1 of Case 21CM380
Plea of " GUILTY  " entered on Count #3 of Case 21CF135

Factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the pleas, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgments of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads in and dismisses Counts #3 and #4-Case #21CF623, Counts #1 and #3 and #5-Case #21CF624, Counts #1 and #2-Case #21CF135, Counts #1 and #2-Case #22CM10. Further, the Court reads in an uncharged referral (DA Case #22JE371) with a date of violation of 1/12/2022 for charges of five counts of Felony Bailjumping and two counts of Misdemeanor Bailjumping, and thereafter bars further prosecution of this referral. 


In Case #21CF623 on Counts #1 and #2 each the Court sentences Mr. Reed to 3 years Imprisonment, consisting of 2 years Initial Confinement and  1 year Extended Supervision.  These sentences are concurrent to each other and to cases #21CF624, #21CT380, #21CF135, but consecutive to any other sentences. 
The Court finds that the Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program "Boot Camp".
The Court finds that the Defendant is not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
The Court gives 0 days credit for time already served. The Court grants counsel thirty days to file a stipulation or a request as to any days credit that are applicable. 


In Case #21CF624 on Counts #2 and #4 each the Court sentences Mr. Reed to 2 years Imprisonment, consisting of 1 year Initial Confinement and  1 year Extended Supervision.  These sentences are concurrent to each other and to cases #21CF623, #21CT380, #21CF135, but consecutive to any other sentences. 
The Court finds that the Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program "Boot Camp".
The Court finds that the Defendant is not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
The Court gives 0 days credit for time already served. The Court grants counsel thirty days to file a stipulation or a request as to any days credit that are applicable. 


The Court orders as conditions of Extended Supervision on both cases:
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with treatment recommendations per the Agent
--to undergo assessment and treatment per the Agent
--to attempt to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program per Agent
--no contact with any named victims in any case files
--in Case #21CF263-Count #1: to pay restitution of $4,000 to Victim 1
--in Case #21CF624-Count #2: to pay restitution of $10,587.65 to Menards
--in Case #21CF624-Count #2: to pay restitution of $400 to Ace Hardware; this restitution is related to read-in case #22CM10
--to comply with DNA sample provision 
--to pay costs, fees, and surcharges

In Case #21CM380 the Court sentences Mr. Reed to serve 6 months Jail, to be served in the Wisconsin Prison System, concurrent with Cases #21CF623, #21CF624, #21CF135, but consecutive to any other sentences. 
Days credit for time already served:  0 days. The Court grants counsel thirty days to file a stipulation or a request as to any days credit that are applicable. 
The Court orders entry of a civil judgment for costs and surcharges court financial obligations.
The Court orders entry of a civil judgment for restitution in the amount of $364.50 in favor of Victim 1.  


In Case #21CF135 the Court sentences Mr. Reed to serve 6 months Jail, to be served in the Wisconsin Prison System, concurrent with Cases #21CF623, #21CF624, #21CM380, but consecutive to any other sentences. 
Days credit for time already served:  0 days. The Court grants counsel thirty days to file a stipulation or a request as to any days credit that are applicable. 
The Court orders entry of a civil judgment for costs and surcharges court financial obligations.

Felony Firearm and Voting-rights prohibitions/warnings given
The Explanation of Determinate Sentence forms are to be mailed to the Defendant at the prison. 
recess 12:37pm
